<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf68b29ab-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10317"><num value="10317">§ 10317.</num><heading> Loss of lien and right to wages</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A master or seaman by any agreement other than one provided for in this chapter may not forfeit the master’s or seaman’s lien on the vessel or be deprived of a remedy to which the master or seaman otherwise would be entitled for the recovery of wages. A stipulation in an agreement inconsistent with this chapter, or a stipulation by which a seaman consents to abandon a right to wages if the vessel is lost, or to abandon a right the seaman may have or obtain in the nature of salvage, is void.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf68b29ac-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/568">97 Stat. 568</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
